               <p>I was sitting at the door, about a quarter after nine, and I saw this prisoner turn the corner with a bundle of things under his arm; I lost sight of him; Mrs. Tranfield lives in Piccadilly, four hundred yards from Hyde-park-corner; I caught him in the middle of the road, near Hyde-park-corner; he had that bundle of clothes.</p>
